CI/CD Pipeline step by step i use Jenkins :
GitHub    â†’     Jenkins      â†’  Docker Hub   â†’  EC2 VM
 push         build & push                  pull & restart

When you push code:
1)Jenkins pulls code
2)Builds Docker images //frontend,backed 
3)Pushes to Docker Hub
4)SSH into EC2
5)docker-compose pull
6)docker-compose up -d

commands:
sudo apt update
sudo apt install openjdk-17-jdk -y
java -version

curl -fsSL https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable/jenkins.io-2026.key | sudo tee \
/usr/share/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc > /dev/null
echo deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc] \
https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable binary/ | sudo tee \
/etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list > /dev/null

sudo apt update

sudo apt install jenkins -y
sudo systemctl start Jenkins

sudo systemctl enable Jenkins
sudo systemctl status Jenkins


âš ï¸ IMPORTANT (Port Conflict Fix):
By default Jenkins runs on 8080.
If your backend Docker container is already using 8080, Jenkins will fail.

sudo lsof -i :8080       // If already used â†’ change Jenkins port to 8081:

sudo systemctl edit Jenkins  // add
[Service]
Environment="JENKINS_PORT=8081"

sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl restart Jenkins

http://YOUR_PUBLIC_IP:8081 //Access Jenkins

sudo cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword   //Get Initial Admin Password


